and is certified Triple Platinum in Canada. His follow-up single, “Fireproof”, was released in the Spring and has already gone Gold as it continues to make its way up the Canadian radio charts. Coleman has crafted a unique musical style, incorporating elements of folk, rock, dance and pop and fusing electronic music with organic instrumentation. He was nominated for Breakthrough Artist of the Year at the 2016 Juno Awards in addition to receiving 3 iHeartRadio MMVA nominations. 
 
Coleman has spent the past year on the road, touring North America with Robert Delong last fall before completing a US headline tour in early 2016, which concluded with a sold out show at The Troubadour in LA. He also supported Twenty One Pilots on their Spring Canadian tour and just completed a Summer full of festival appearances, including Bottlerock, Calgary Stampede, The Great Escape (UK), Hangout Fest, Firefly, Summerfest, Ottawa Blues Festival, Pemberton, Wayhome, K Days, Osheaga, Billboard Fest, Rifflandia and more. He also performed on Parliament Hill as part of CBC’s nationally televised Canada Day celebration and recorded a Brazilian version of his hit single, “2 Heads”, for CBC to use in their broadcast of the Rio Olympics. 
 
Coleman Hell’s debut album, Summerland, will be available this Fall via 604 Records in Canada and Columbia Records internationally.
